    "id": "2079098626530545750",
    "text": "My house was built on a foundation of wood. It works well normally because I put a whole lot of wood under it. \n\nBut termites came and started to eat the wood. Slowly but surely, the wood got thinned out. My house still was fine. Everybody was still living inside comfortably. I ignored the termites since nobody was complaining and didn't add more wood back. The new narrative was a glut of wood anyway, don't worry.\n\nSuddenly, a big storm came. My shaky wooden foundation crumbled. All hell broke loose. But my neighbour next door with cement foundation was fine. \n\nHow I wish I fixed that termite issue when I had the time.\n\nIYKYK.\n\n#oott",
