  {
    "id": "2079110831443431838",
    "text": "The oil market has already gone through 2 iterations of this, but I’ll just say it again. \n\nThe conflict over the Strait of Hormuz won’t have an in-between solution. Either Iran controls it or it doesn’t. \n\nThe US cannot allow Iran to control it, toll it, or whatever because it would make it the most powerful oil producer in the world. \n\nIn the near term, prices will continue to trade off of headlines, but when the reality that this is an all or nothing sets in, it will be too late.",
